{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"body":"REOPENING — premature close. My import fix (Gerrit 529, merged) correctly fixed the module-scope import, but the optionality clean-core-wheel job on the merged main tip (57dde4b16) STILL FAILS at a LATER step (degradation-path tests) that was previously MASKED behind the import error. Two failures in tests/interfaces/store/test_llm_optionality.py: (1) line 163 'review_code is fail-safe (off by default) -> exit 0' got exit 1; (2) test_mcp_operations_error_cleanly_when_gated_on_but_extra_absent 'DID NOT RAISE'. These SKIP when the agents extra is installed, so my local (extras-present) run never exercised them. Root lesson: the Verified vote (gerrit-verify) does NOT run the clean-wheel job, so Verified+1 did not prove optionality green. Investigating whether these are my regression or pre-existing-unmasked breakage."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783787221573407001,"uuid":"a6f1eedf-a204-4c34-9e0f-92e350e94d4e"}